gr.forth.ics.swkm.model2
Interface Triple

public interface Triple

An RDF triple. A triple must always be contained in at least one named graph, or else it is deleted from its model.

A triple imposes some constraints on its parts:

  • The subject can be either a Resource or a BlankNode
  • The predicate can only be a Resource
  • The object can be either a Resource, a BlankNode, or a LiteralNode.
So, the subject is modelled as an ObjectNode (which is the super type of Resources and BlankNodes), the predicate is modelled as a Resource, and the object is modelled as an RdfNode (which is the super type of Resources, BlankNodes and LiteralNodes).

Author:
Andreou Dimitris, email: jim.andreou (at) gmail (dot) com

boolean delete()
Deletes this triple from its owner model.

Important: After triple deletions, the typing of the nodes is guarranteed to remain valid and consistent, but it is no longer guarranteed to be minimal. Strongly consider invoking Model.retypeNodes() after triple deletions (see the method specification for further details).
